        descLong: "Alembic is the migration tool for SQLAlchemy. The setup story is short — `alembic init`, point env.py at your declarative `metadata`, run `revision --autogenerate` — but the polish that prevents pain later (naming conventions, env-driven URLs, SQLite batch mode, CI gates) is what separates \"demo\" from \"production\". The three examples solve the SAME task — bootstrap Alembic on an app with existing models and produce the first migration — at increasing depths: minimal setup → multi-env config + naming conventions → programmatic API + tests that verify reversibility.",
